{{italic title}}
{{Orphan|date=February 2009}}
'''''Flute's Journey: The Life of a Wood Thrush''''' is a children's picture book by [[Lynne Cherry]].

==Plot summary==
The book tells the first year of a [[wood thrush|wood thrush's]] life starting from it hatching in a forest that is in [[Maryland]]. Two children see the bird when it is young and calls it Flute. The children wait for Flute to return from [[bird migration|migration]] and watch him and his [[Mating|mate]] build a [[bird nest|nest]] and raise their young. In Flute's travels, he encounters many dangers. The [[Egg (biology)|eggs]] and [[nestlings]] are at more of a risk.

==Reception==
A review in the book ''Gotcha!: Nonfiction Booktalks to Get Kids Excited about Reading'' says, "Whether or not you know much about songbirds and the dangers they face, this book is great reading, and it includes ideas for things that kids can do to help them. The illustration of Flute's mother feeding her babies a worm is a good one to show."<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=FQrW4WYRKs4C&pg=PA44&dq=Flute%27s+Journey:+The+Life+of+a+Wood+Thrush&lr=#PPA44,M1  Gotcha!: Nonfiction Booktalks to Get Kids Excited about Reading]</ref> Books use the book for activities for kids to do.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=q8oYWI7KFi0C&pg=PA52&dq=Flute%27s+Journey:+The+Life+of+a+Wood+Thrush&lr= Writing with Authors Kids Love]</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=KPNotFXqXQ0C&pg=PA178&dq=Flute%27s+Journey:+The+Life+of+a+Wood+Thrush&lr= Young Adult Literature in the Classroom]</ref> The book focused national media attention on conservation efforts to save the Belt Woods in Maryland.<ref>[http://www.greenhousenet.org/network/dcarea.html Green House Network] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081227091029/http://www.greenhousenet.org/network/dcarea.html |date=December 27, 2008 }}</ref>

